    <descript>
      <abstract>LIDAR-derived binary (.las) files containing classified points of all returns.  We have 7 classifications Unclassified, Ground, Low Noise, Water, Ignore Ground, Bridge Decks and High Noise. The files are delivered in 3,000ft by 3,000ft tiles. These files are in ASPRS ver 1.4 format.</abstract>
      <purpose>LiDAR terrain mapping to the Colorado Water Conservation Board (CWCB) for all or portions of Garfield, Eagle, Summit,
Clear Creek, Gilpin, Douglas and Jefferson Counties. Approximately 6,150 square miles.</purpose>
